1
00:00:01,201 --> 00:00:02,736
Do you like me?

2
00:00:05,572 --> 00:00:06,840
Why is he asking me that?

3
00:00:07,474 --> 00:00:09,810
Wait, calm down. Why is this happening?

4
00:00:10,377 --> 00:00:14,915
I've always aimed for a normal average
work and love life.

5
00:00:14,948 --> 00:00:17,317
But my boss is
a devilish editor-in-chief.

6
00:00:17,351 --> 00:00:21,288
I'm also being swept away
by her cute puppy-like brother.

7
00:00:22,623 --> 00:00:24,258
I, well...

8
00:00:25,292 --> 00:00:27,027
Um, well...

9
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:27,928
You hate me?

10
00:00:27,961 --> 00:00:29,463
No, not at all!

11
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,465
I'm so relieved.

12
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:35,869
I put you through so much trouble.

13
00:00:36,803 --> 00:00:37,771
I thought you hated me.

14
00:00:38,639 --> 00:00:41,008
Oh, that's what he meant.

15
00:00:41,441 --> 00:00:43,076
Since you don't hate me...

16
00:00:44,244 --> 00:00:45,012
Here.

17
00:00:45,045 --> 00:00:47,080
Between Sky and Earth

18
00:00:47,147 --> 00:00:48,882
Your photography exhibition?

19
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:49,716
Yeah.

20
00:00:52,853 --> 00:00:53,620
Hey, Suzuki!

21
00:00:54,354 --> 00:00:55,589
Get in here.

22
00:00:55,622 --> 00:00:57,824
Sorry! Bye.

23
00:00:58,158 --> 00:00:59,893
It starts next week!

24
00:00:59,927 --> 00:01:02,095
Thanks. Sorry.

25
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:05,966
Hi.

26
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:09,970
Mitsuki Seo is really popular
these days.

27
00:01:10,604 --> 00:01:13,340
As both an athlete and a model.

28
00:01:13,373 --> 00:01:15,042
World Championships are coming up.

29
00:01:15,642 --> 00:01:18,679
All eyes will be on her
once this feature gets out.

30
00:01:20,213 --> 00:01:21,281
Next week, huh.

31
00:01:22,816 --> 00:01:25,986
It'd be way too dangerous.

32
00:01:27,387 --> 00:01:31,959
It's like finding a wet little puppy.

33
00:01:33,994 --> 00:01:34,828
Are you lost?

34
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:40,801
Eat up, Jun.

35
00:01:44,838 --> 00:01:47,975
But you know its owner
will show up some day...

36
00:01:48,008 --> 00:01:50,043
- Chopin!
- Chopin!

37
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:53,880
- Chopin!
- Thank you so much.

38
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:55,649
Let's go.

39
00:01:57,884 --> 00:01:58,952
Jun...

40
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:02,990
And your heart is irreparably broken.

41
00:02:03,523 --> 00:02:06,994
No, it's too dangerous.
The puppy brother of a devil boss.

42
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:08,562
I mustn't pick it up.

43
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:09,596
No, pick it up.

44
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:12,899
Stop daydreaming.
Help change the set.

45
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,301
Sorry. Oops!

46
00:02:15,235 --> 00:02:18,305
A few days later

47
00:02:18,905 --> 00:02:22,209
- Watch out, move!
- Sorry!

48
00:02:33,086 --> 00:02:34,488
Something going on?

49
00:02:34,521 --> 00:02:35,989
Final proofing is next week.

50
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:37,257
Final proofing?

51
00:02:37,724 --> 00:02:40,060
The final deadline.

52
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:44,064
The editors create the pages,
and the editor-in-chief checks them.

53
00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:47,934
It's then stamped "OK" or
"OK with corrections."

54
00:02:47,968 --> 00:02:51,071
"OK" means it's perfect
and can be printed.

55
00:02:51,438 --> 00:02:55,275
"OK with corrections" means
there are some corrections

56
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:57,010
that the printers must fix.

57
00:02:57,044 --> 00:02:59,146
Either way, it's on to the printers.

58
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:05,485
Mr. Nakazawa seems relaxed.

59
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:08,188
He's already done with his pages.

60
00:03:08,221 --> 00:03:10,557
You know, the shoot you did
with Mitsuki Seo.

61
00:03:10,924 --> 00:03:12,459
That was Mitsuki Seo?

62
00:03:12,993 --> 00:03:14,795
The judo athlete?

63
00:03:14,828 --> 00:03:16,963
I couldn't tell,
she was so dressed up.

64
00:03:17,230 --> 00:03:19,166
She's known to model quite a lot.

65
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,634
Talking about Mitsuki Seo?

66
00:03:21,401 --> 00:03:25,472
She'd hurt her shoulder,
but she's about to make her comeback.

67
00:03:25,839 --> 00:03:30,710
I've made a pretty good feature
for the first ever issue of Miyavi.

68
00:03:30,744 --> 00:03:32,612
- You seem happy.
- So what?

69
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:37,317
I'm actually a huge fan
of the father, Mitsuharu Seo.

70
00:03:37,784 --> 00:03:41,188
A great judoka, passionate about
winning with an ippon.

71
00:03:41,254 --> 00:03:44,524
Mitsuki Seo totally follows
after her father's footsteps.

72
00:03:44,858 --> 00:03:48,562
It's a bit early,
but let's begin the meeting.

73
00:03:50,263 --> 00:03:52,365
Anything else to report?

74
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,701
I guess that's it then.

75
00:03:55,035 --> 00:03:57,637
One week until
Miyavi's first final proof.

76
00:03:57,671 --> 00:03:58,805
We can do it!

77
00:03:59,339 --> 00:04:01,741
May we have a word from you?

78
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,444
Mitsuki Seo's interview
for the culture page.

79
00:04:05,512 --> 00:04:07,280
Change it to Sawako Kobayakawa.

80
00:04:08,615 --> 00:04:09,916
Change the interview?

81
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,019
That's all.

82
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:15,722
Redo the whole feature?

83
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:16,690
Do you have a problem?

84
00:04:17,557 --> 00:04:19,092
Wait a minute, I don't get it.

85
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:23,964
We've already interviewed and shot
Mitsuki Seo for the first issue.

86
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:28,201
You said okay
during the editorial meeting.

87
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:31,571
You can't scrap it now.

88
00:04:32,405 --> 00:04:34,307
Her shoulder hasn't recovered yet.

89
00:04:35,075 --> 00:04:37,144
Didn't you notice her posing?

90
00:04:38,512 --> 00:04:41,047
She won't be
in next month's championships.

91
00:04:42,582 --> 00:04:46,553
I see. I understand your reasoning.

92
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:48,522
- Let's change it.
- Wait.

93
00:04:48,555 --> 00:04:51,124
But she's prepared to compete in it.

94
00:04:51,158 --> 00:04:55,428
Don't be so naive. We chose her
betting on her huge comeback.

95
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,298
If she can't, we can't feature her.

96
00:04:58,331 --> 00:04:59,299
Right?

97
00:04:59,332 --> 00:05:00,901
She's gone, but still.

98
00:05:01,835 --> 00:05:05,472
One week until final proofing.
We don't have a minute to lose.

99
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:11,011
Who is Sawako Kobayakawa,
the new feature?

100
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:13,613
A global economy analyst.

101
00:05:14,181 --> 00:05:16,883
It's said one word from her
can rock the stock market.

102
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:18,752
She smells of money.

103
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:20,153
Ms. Horai must love her.

104
00:05:20,554 --> 00:05:23,490
I bet there's a reason behind it.

105
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:25,091
A reason?

106
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:30,964
What I thought was an errand for
a date was for negotiating a designer.

107
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:31,865
50 million.

108
00:05:32,132 --> 00:05:35,569
And she sent me to negotiate
with a manga artist

109
00:05:35,602 --> 00:05:36,870
and landed a huge ad sales.

110
00:05:36,903 --> 00:05:37,971
60 million.

111
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:40,941
There's always been a reason.

112
00:05:41,308 --> 00:05:42,576
So I'm guessing...

113
00:05:42,909 --> 00:05:43,677
That scared me.

114
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,948
I'm never going to interview
Sawako Kobayakawa.

115
00:05:49,449 --> 00:05:51,418
- But...
- Scary!

116
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:53,253
Nakazawa is really mad now.

117
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,622
You can't blame him though.

118
00:05:55,655 --> 00:05:59,559
She made me change the entire layout
of a finished page.

119
00:05:59,593 --> 00:06:01,294
She did that to me, too.

120
00:06:01,328 --> 00:06:04,231
I had to change every outfit
the day of a shoot.

121
00:06:04,264 --> 00:06:09,169
That devil editor-in-chief
only thinks of us as tools.

122
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:11,204
- Pretty harsh.
- Duh.

123
00:06:11,238 --> 00:06:14,007
I don't care if she worked
in France or what.

124
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:17,377
But publishing the first issue
in just two months?

125
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:20,080
Does she even realize
how impossible that is?

126
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:22,983
Why doesn't she do it herself, huh?

127
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:32,492
Jesus...

128
00:06:34,427 --> 00:06:37,664
I'm meeting Sawako Kobayakawa
tomorrow morning.

129
00:06:37,697 --> 00:06:38,832
8:30, got it?

130
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,636
I was just...

131
00:06:42,669 --> 00:06:44,170
You heard her.

132
00:06:45,839 --> 00:06:47,774
We're all fed up with you.

133
00:06:48,541 --> 00:06:49,342
So?

134
00:06:49,376 --> 00:06:53,213
Unless you change your ways,
we can't work with you.

135
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,382
That's being a bit harsh, isn't it?

136
00:06:55,415 --> 00:07:00,353
Either you quit, or we quit.

137
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,956
Which will it be?

138
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:09,663
Interesting.

139
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:34,788
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

140
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:35,088
Between Sky and Earth

141
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:38,091
Magnificent.
I feel the message of the era.

142
00:07:38,658 --> 00:07:40,527
It's just a cicada shell.

143
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:43,029
It's the solitude of modern times.

144
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:45,432
So, how's the day after tomorrow
at three?

145
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,266
Sure.

146
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:48,101
Thanks. You must be busy.

147
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,203
It's fine,
I'm not coming here every day.

148
00:07:50,236 --> 00:07:52,005
Will your father be coming here?

149
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:53,907
No, I don't think so.

150
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:55,742
Yes, Kanazawa is a bit far.

151
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,678
If he does, tell him I said hello.

152
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:00,980
Okay, see you in two days then.

153
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:06,586
My father, huh?

154
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:08,988
Seo Judo Dojo

155
00:08:46,793 --> 00:08:48,495
I don't understand it.

156
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:52,332
With your brains and experience,
you could do anything.

157
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:54,667
Why are you in publishing?

158
00:08:55,769 --> 00:08:58,671
It's an honor that you believe so.

159
00:08:59,139 --> 00:09:02,142
For the time being,
I'm going to focus on Miyavi.

160
00:09:08,114 --> 00:09:09,482
Out of spite for your father?

161
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:15,655
The Horai Group is more than just
a regional company now.

162
00:09:16,156 --> 00:09:20,260
Your father must want your help.

163
00:09:20,627 --> 00:09:22,095
What are they talking about?

164
00:09:22,529 --> 00:09:24,898
Does it have to do
with what's going on?

165
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:28,835
But if there's a good reason
like the other times,

166
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:32,338
I bet the others will understand, too.

167
00:09:34,808 --> 00:09:38,678
Ms. Horai, you shouldn't be out here
jogging like this.

168
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:42,415
Mr. Handa and Ms. Izumi
were the only ones that came today.

169
00:09:44,184 --> 00:09:45,852
Do you hear me?

170
00:09:46,553 --> 00:09:48,788
It's a week away from final proofs.

171
00:09:48,822 --> 00:09:52,158
Then find me some new editors.

172
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:55,094
Hold on a second.

173
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:57,964
I knew it!

174
00:09:57,997 --> 00:10:00,266
Ms. Kobayakawa, long time no see!

175
00:10:02,202 --> 00:10:03,069
You are...?

176
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:05,171
Takahashi, editor-in-chief of Zeal.

177
00:10:08,908 --> 00:10:10,743
You must know Ms. Horai then.

178
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,015
Oh, Reiko.

179
00:10:16,049 --> 00:10:19,285
Are you the wild vegetable picker?
Here to drop them off?

180
00:10:19,319 --> 00:10:22,956
The soba shop here offers
delicious wild vegetables.

181
00:10:22,989 --> 00:10:24,090
Shall we go?

182
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:26,192
What a pretty wild vegetable picker.

183
00:10:26,226 --> 00:10:29,462
Shut up!
I'll break those long legs of yours.

184
00:10:30,763 --> 00:10:31,698
Excuse me.

185
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,635
May I have a minute?

186
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:38,605
Why Reiko is close
with Ms. Kobayakawa?

187
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:41,674
Why would I know?

188
00:10:42,242 --> 00:10:44,644
There has to be some secret.

189
00:10:45,078 --> 00:10:47,847
Like there's money involved
or something.

190
00:10:48,248 --> 00:10:50,250
70 million yen is my guess.

191
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:54,687
And that's why she's changing
the feature interview.

192
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:57,490
You're pretty stupid.

193
00:10:58,124 --> 00:11:00,393
I'm the rival editor-in-chief,
remember?

194
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:04,664
Don't worry, I won't steal her idea.

195
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:12,438
I'm dead tired.

196
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:24,017
It's the lost puppy again.

197
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:29,055
He's so cute.

198
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,661
Get a hold of yourself.

199
00:11:39,499 --> 00:11:40,500
The mean senpai.

200
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:43,069
Sorry.

201
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,672
Oh, you're Suzuki's...

202
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,310
She's probably left by now.

203
00:11:50,343 --> 00:11:54,881
Could you give this to her then?

204
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:56,683
I'm doing a photo exhibition.

205
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,217
I'll be at the gallery
during these hours.

206
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,853
Come during these hours

207
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:05,825
If I remember.

208
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:08,194
Bye.

209
00:12:11,998 --> 00:12:15,134
The mean senpai
is actually pretty nice.

210
00:12:22,775 --> 00:12:24,010
Ouch...

211
00:12:24,978 --> 00:12:27,180
It's because I jogged yesterday.

212
00:12:30,516 --> 00:12:31,551
I'm cramped!

213
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:38,725
Why are you alone?

214
00:12:39,325 --> 00:12:42,595
Where's Nakazawa and Wada?
Why didn't you bring them?

215
00:12:42,662 --> 00:12:44,464
As if I could.

216
00:12:44,697 --> 00:12:46,132
Good morning!

217
00:12:46,165 --> 00:12:47,033
Good morning.

218
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,802
So, where are my new editors?

219
00:12:50,136 --> 00:12:51,137
New editors?

220
00:12:51,404 --> 00:12:54,073
My attendant was supposed to
get me some.

221
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:57,944
Ms. Horai, won't you apologize
to Mr. Nakazawa and the others?

222
00:12:57,977 --> 00:13:01,180
Just ask them, and they'll come back.

223
00:13:01,214 --> 00:13:02,782
Suzuki!

224
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,822
Remember how much my begging costs?

225
00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:12,992
50 million yen.

226
00:13:16,195 --> 00:13:17,697
Forgive us!

227
00:13:23,436 --> 00:13:24,270
Devil.

228
00:13:25,605 --> 00:13:29,142
Suzuki. How's the editor-in-chief?

229
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:32,545
She told us to hire new editors.

230
00:13:32,578 --> 00:13:36,716
Please, apologize to her
and come back.

231
00:13:37,283 --> 00:13:39,085
Why would I?

232
00:13:39,118 --> 00:13:40,920
Just come back.

233
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,921
No way!

234
00:13:41,954 --> 00:13:46,759
Until she apologizes,
we are not coming back.

235
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:53,499
- Let's just do what we can.
- Yes.

236
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:56,836
Let's prepare for the interview
with Sawako Kobayakawa.

237
00:13:56,869 --> 00:13:58,705
Ms. Suzuki, book a studio.

238
00:13:58,738 --> 00:14:00,973
And a cameraman, stylist,
and make-up.

239
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:02,341
- Do it.
- Okay.

240
00:14:02,375 --> 00:14:04,610
- How do I do that?
- What about me?

241
00:14:05,378 --> 00:14:06,512
Phone!

242
00:14:06,779 --> 00:14:08,314
What's wrong with your legs?

243
00:14:09,048 --> 00:14:10,850
Yes, Miyavi Editorial.

244
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:13,953
One moment please.

245
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:18,257
The printers are asking about
the poster sample.

246
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,360
- The poster!
- The poster? What?

247
00:14:21,394 --> 00:14:24,097
What is it? Huh?

248
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:26,999
- I'm scared, what?
- What are you checking?

249
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:28,134
Oh no.

250
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:30,670
It still says "Mitsuki Seo."

251
00:14:31,571 --> 00:14:32,805
Stop the printing!

252
00:14:32,839 --> 00:14:34,907
Stop, don't print it!

253
00:14:34,941 --> 00:14:37,276
We're not going to make it.

254
00:14:37,310 --> 00:14:39,145
I'm running to the printers.

255
00:14:39,178 --> 00:14:41,647
- The printers?
- What about me?

256
00:14:41,681 --> 00:14:43,116
Book a studio!

257
00:14:43,449 --> 00:14:47,220
Oh no! And fix the digital ads!

258
00:14:47,253 --> 00:14:49,322
They all say "Mitsuki Seo."

259
00:14:49,355 --> 00:14:50,990
You can do that, right?

260
00:14:51,023 --> 00:14:52,725
Not the PDF, the JPEG.

261
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:54,894
The J... what?

262
00:14:54,927 --> 00:14:59,098
The J Park. Where they play ball.

263
00:14:59,132 --> 00:15:00,633
I'm dead.

264
00:15:01,768 --> 00:15:03,736
- Huh?
- Are you okay?

265
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:05,671
A bit overwhelmed.

266
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:11,377
Ms. Kazumi?

267
00:15:11,778 --> 00:15:13,913
Please, I need your help.

268
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,849
Okay, fine.

269
00:15:16,883 --> 00:15:20,052
Come tonight to where I tell you.

270
00:15:22,355 --> 00:15:24,657
- Suzuki!
- There you are.

271
00:15:25,124 --> 00:15:27,126
Over here. Come on.

272
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:29,595
I can't anymore.

273
00:15:30,663 --> 00:15:33,766
We need you back or...

274
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,702
Who cares about that right now?

275
00:15:36,736 --> 00:15:38,171
Come on.

276
00:15:38,204 --> 00:15:39,772
Now, have a seat.

277
00:15:40,807 --> 00:15:42,341
No, over here.

278
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:55,721
You don't mean...

279
00:15:56,088 --> 00:15:58,391
Over here!

280
00:15:58,825 --> 00:16:01,794
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

281
00:16:01,828 --> 00:16:04,697
I'm not used to these things.

282
00:16:05,164 --> 00:16:06,132
A mixer?

283
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:07,166
Nami?

284
00:16:07,867 --> 00:16:08,668
Why are you here?

285
00:16:09,101 --> 00:16:10,570
Why are you?

286
00:16:10,603 --> 00:16:14,140
Huh?
You look like Suzuki's boyfriend...

287
00:16:14,173 --> 00:16:17,777
No, he's not.
Remember? He was more snowman-like.

288
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:19,245
Was he?

289
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:20,913
You know her?

290
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:23,683
Yeah, she's actually my...

291
00:16:25,384 --> 00:16:27,920
Friend. Just a friend.

292
00:16:28,788 --> 00:16:31,691
Smiling like a puppy again.

293
00:16:32,058 --> 00:16:34,493
And I was trying
to stay away from him.

294
00:16:34,527 --> 00:16:37,563
You're a photographer, right?

295
00:16:37,597 --> 00:16:40,366
Maybe you can do some of our shoots.

296
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:41,934
That's abuse of authority.

297
00:16:41,968 --> 00:16:44,036
Not as much as our editor-in-chief.

298
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:46,806
Have you seen the devil before?

299
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:49,475
Our boss is the devil herself.

300
00:16:50,142 --> 00:16:52,845
She said to swap interviews
a week before deadline.

301
00:16:53,112 --> 00:16:55,081
Can you believe it?

302
00:16:55,581 --> 00:16:56,449
A devil, huh.

303
00:16:56,649 --> 00:16:58,985
I'm even thinking about quitting now.

304
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,286
You don't mean that.

305
00:17:00,319 --> 00:17:03,489
You're quitting to succeed
the family business, right?

306
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:04,590
Some day.

307
00:17:04,891 --> 00:17:05,691
Family business?

308
00:17:05,725 --> 00:17:07,159
In Kanazawa, huh?

309
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:09,495
His family is filthy rich.

310
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:12,164
Your family in Kanazawa?

311
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:14,200
It's a rural place.

312
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:17,036
So they expect the son
to carry on the business.

313
00:17:17,069 --> 00:17:21,040
That means
it's Ms. Horai's family, too.

314
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:25,211
Your father must want your help.

315
00:17:26,312 --> 00:17:29,916
But they're letting me do what I want
until then.

316
00:17:31,951 --> 00:17:34,620
I'm holding an exhibition right now.

317
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:38,391
Here. Come stop by if you can.

318
00:17:38,424 --> 00:17:39,825
Thank you.

319
00:17:44,664 --> 00:17:46,499
Since you don't hate me...

320
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,369
Your photography exhibition?

321
00:17:52,939 --> 00:17:54,307
I knew it.

322
00:17:55,808 --> 00:17:58,644
I'm nothing special to him.

323
00:17:58,678 --> 00:17:59,912
Yeah, thanks.

324
00:18:01,814 --> 00:18:03,549
- It's so cold.
- Yeah.

325
00:18:05,618 --> 00:18:07,620
I'm a bit tipsy.

326
00:18:07,653 --> 00:18:08,821
Are you okay?

327
00:18:09,789 --> 00:18:11,657
I must've had a bit too much.

328
00:18:11,691 --> 00:18:12,959
I'm going now.

329
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:22,902
This way.

330
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:24,003
No, this way!

331
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:27,239
- You made me spill it!
- I'm sorry.

332
00:18:27,573 --> 00:18:29,241
Are you okay, Jurina?

333
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:30,609
I'm sorry.

334
00:18:30,643 --> 00:18:32,545
Hey, I'm drenched.

335
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,514
No, you're not.

336
00:18:39,218 --> 00:18:42,054
She said she's drenched.

337
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:56,202
She said she was sorry.

338
00:18:56,702 --> 00:18:58,504
- What the heck?
- Who are you?

339
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:01,974
A UFO!

340
00:19:33,072 --> 00:19:35,007
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

341
00:19:38,778 --> 00:19:41,147
Thanks.

342
00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:43,649
I'll be going now.

343
00:19:44,417 --> 00:19:47,353
I'll walk you to the station.
It's a nice night.

344
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,388
No, I'll be fine.

345
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:54,226
Seems like
you're having a hard time at work.

346
00:19:55,995 --> 00:19:56,829
Yeah.

347
00:19:57,563 --> 00:20:00,666
But you haven't quit yet.

348
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:04,703
Thought I'd give an average effort.

349
00:20:06,672 --> 00:20:08,040
What about you?

350
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,776
Are you going to quit photography?

351
00:20:11,143 --> 00:20:12,144
One day.

352
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:17,216
Oh yeah, give me your number again.

353
00:20:17,249 --> 00:20:18,384
I deleted it.

354
00:20:20,953 --> 00:20:22,788
You don't need it.

355
00:20:23,022 --> 00:20:24,457
We're nothing now.

356
00:20:26,692 --> 00:20:28,360
But let me know if you can come...

357
00:20:28,394 --> 00:20:31,163
I'm busy,
so I don't think I'll be able to.

358
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:32,998
Sorry.

359
00:20:42,308 --> 00:20:44,243
I still don't understand why.

360
00:20:44,276 --> 00:20:46,278
Why would I need you to?

361
00:20:46,312 --> 00:20:48,047
It's too much for me!

362
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:50,015
I'm never going back.

363
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:52,818
So you had Suzuki
be your fake girlfriend.

364
00:20:53,319 --> 00:20:55,921
That girl came. What's her name, Nami?

365
00:20:55,955 --> 00:20:56,722
When?

366
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:04,130
Let me introduce you.

367
00:21:04,663 --> 00:21:07,466
The latest member of our Miyavi team.

368
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,468
Mr. Takashi Ogasawara.

369
00:21:10,469 --> 00:21:13,539
I'm Ogasawara. I'll do my best.

370
00:21:13,806 --> 00:21:18,277
If there's anything
you don't understand, ask these two.

371
00:21:22,348 --> 00:21:23,883
Nice to meet you.

372
00:21:24,383 --> 00:21:25,818
Nice to meet you too.

373
00:21:25,851 --> 00:21:27,119
Suzuki.

374
00:21:27,153 --> 00:21:29,421
Get me a tart from Patisserie Chante.

375
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:31,290
And grab me a taxi too.

376
00:21:47,273 --> 00:21:48,073
There you are.

377
00:21:49,808 --> 00:21:50,776
It's you.

378
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:52,211
Pick up your phone, jeez.

379
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:55,948
Do you realize the trouble
you're putting us through?

380
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:57,950
Please come back.

381
00:21:58,384 --> 00:21:59,385
Never.

382
00:22:00,519 --> 00:22:02,922
We won't get the first issue
out in time.

383
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:05,024
Take responsibility for your work.

384
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:09,828
What would you know?
You've never published a book before.

385
00:22:10,963 --> 00:22:13,232
You just do what you're told to do.

386
00:22:15,301 --> 00:22:17,136
That Mitsuki Seo feature.

387
00:22:17,603 --> 00:22:22,107
I've covered them ever since I became
an editor, waiting for my chance.

388
00:22:23,108 --> 00:22:26,378
I thought the first issue of Miyavi
would be best for it.

389
00:22:26,412 --> 00:22:30,583
She was happy that the feature
would be right before her comeback.

390
00:22:31,917 --> 00:22:34,253
But that cyborg woman...

391
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:37,389
Squashed it like it was nothing.

392
00:22:39,058 --> 00:22:40,392
I'm never going back.

393
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,395
Gotta go. The movie is starting.

394
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:45,197
Wait.

395
00:22:50,769 --> 00:22:51,804
Sis?

396
00:22:54,673 --> 00:22:56,375
I thought you were busy.

397
00:22:57,376 --> 00:23:00,679
Look at all those flowers sent to you.

398
00:23:01,747 --> 00:23:03,716
Yeah, to Dad is more like it.

399
00:23:04,483 --> 00:23:07,386
They say all this superficial stuff

400
00:23:07,419 --> 00:23:09,922
like, "I feel the solitude
of modern times."

401
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:14,026
I'm just enjoying photography.

402
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:16,395
They're buttering up to
the next Horai president.

403
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:18,330
Who cares about that?

404
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:24,770
You should succeed the business,
not me.

405
00:23:25,638 --> 00:23:27,873
You're way more cut out for it
than me.

406
00:23:29,475 --> 00:23:32,111
Wow, a PlayStation2! I want one too!

407
00:23:32,144 --> 00:23:35,547
Reiko deserves it for getting
number one on the national test.

408
00:23:35,814 --> 00:23:36,815
Lucky her.

409
00:23:37,383 --> 00:23:39,151
You should try hard, too.

410
00:23:39,184 --> 00:23:41,053
I hate studying.

411
00:23:42,321 --> 00:23:44,089
He's fine the way he is.

412
00:23:45,124 --> 00:23:47,926
You're the one
who'll fulfill my dreams, Reiko.

413
00:23:48,527 --> 00:23:51,330
I'll be number one again for you,
Daddy.

414
00:23:55,701 --> 00:23:58,103
You haven't been home in a while.

415
00:23:59,238 --> 00:24:00,939
I bet Dad misses you.

416
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:03,509
So you had Suzuki
be your fake girlfriend.

417
00:24:05,577 --> 00:24:08,147
You pretended you wanted me
to persuade Mom.

418
00:24:08,681 --> 00:24:10,949
But it was so I'd go see Dad.

419
00:24:13,419 --> 00:24:14,820
You knew, huh.

420
00:24:15,321 --> 00:24:17,690
I really didn't want
any more matchmakers.

421
00:24:18,424 --> 00:24:21,460
But why didn't you tell me
if you already knew?

422
00:24:22,227 --> 00:24:26,198
It's fine. The Horai family business
is going to be yours.

423
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:43,148
Where's Ms. Haruka?

424
00:24:43,182 --> 00:24:45,884
She went to check tomorrow's studio.

425
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,619
Okay.

426
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:54,159
This Mitsuki Seo interview.
What a great feature.

427
00:24:54,193 --> 00:24:56,028
That was actually scrapped.

428
00:24:57,196 --> 00:24:58,864
What a waste.

429
00:24:59,631 --> 00:25:02,201
Such a wonderful interview.

430
00:25:08,374 --> 00:25:11,010
Repaying My Father by Winning

431
00:25:13,045 --> 00:25:14,413
Ms. Horai, a word.

432
00:25:14,446 --> 00:25:15,381
I have none for you.

433
00:25:15,414 --> 00:25:16,715
But I do.

434
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:19,485
I don't get why you scrapped it.

435
00:25:19,852 --> 00:25:23,655
This interview is really great.

436
00:25:24,056 --> 00:25:25,924
Why is it Sawako Kobayakawa?

437
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:30,929
There's a reason, isn't there?
For 50 or 60 million or something.

438
00:25:30,963 --> 00:25:31,997
Ridiculous.

439
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:33,866
Then why did you scrap it?

440
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,468
Nobody understands your decision.

441
00:25:36,869 --> 00:25:39,204
Why would I need you to?

442
00:25:39,238 --> 00:25:40,272
Because...

443
00:25:42,141 --> 00:25:45,344
Mitsuki Seo agreed with my decision.

444
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:52,284
If the devotion is too strong,

445
00:25:52,317 --> 00:25:55,487
people tend to fabricate
the story they want to see.

446
00:25:57,256 --> 00:25:58,957
You have to take a step back.

447
00:25:59,725 --> 00:26:02,261
To see if you haven't
omitted something.

448
00:26:05,864 --> 00:26:07,366
A step back?

449
00:26:13,439 --> 00:26:16,408
I hear things are hectic.

450
00:26:17,743 --> 00:26:19,912
Yes, I'm sorry for the trouble.

451
00:26:20,479 --> 00:26:23,949
But you have a reason
for doing this, right?

452
00:26:25,884 --> 00:26:27,886
Then stick to it. Don't give in.

453
00:26:28,921 --> 00:26:31,757
Don't worry, I'll take responsibility.

454
00:26:34,326 --> 00:26:36,161
Why don't we go out to eat?

455
00:26:46,338 --> 00:26:48,874
- What are you doing?
- I have to find something.

456
00:26:59,618 --> 00:27:00,919
The Judo Soul Passed Down

457
00:27:00,953 --> 00:27:01,854
Seo Daughter and Father Win Gold

458
00:27:04,089 --> 00:27:05,357
Mitsuharu Seo

459
00:27:12,498 --> 00:27:14,032
Seo's First Victory

460
00:27:18,704 --> 00:27:20,405
That Mitsuki Seo feature.

461
00:27:20,672 --> 00:27:25,244
I've covered them ever since I became
an editor, waiting for my chance.

462
00:27:27,746 --> 00:27:30,048
He researched all this?

463
00:27:35,554 --> 00:27:38,357
7th Consecutive Champion

464
00:27:49,868 --> 00:27:51,236
7th Consecutive Champion

465
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:52,404
Repaying My Father by Winning

466
00:27:52,471 --> 00:27:55,908
Something he's omitted?

467
00:28:02,414 --> 00:28:03,081
6th Consecutive Champion

468
00:28:03,081 --> 00:28:05,651
6th consecutive World Champion?

469
00:28:10,389 --> 00:28:13,358
Tomorrow's interview
is Sawako Kobayakawa.

470
00:28:14,059 --> 00:28:15,561
I get it now.

471
00:28:16,762 --> 00:28:19,131
Sawako Kobayakawa wasn't the reason.

472
00:28:19,831 --> 00:28:20,799
I have to go.

473
00:28:21,433 --> 00:28:22,868
Ms. Suzuki?

474
00:28:34,313 --> 00:28:36,214
You again? Give it up.

475
00:28:36,248 --> 00:28:37,282
I need you to come.

476
00:28:37,749 --> 00:28:40,018
- I'm not going to work...
- To Mitsuki Seo.

477
00:28:46,992 --> 00:28:49,461
I'm going back to the house, Mitsuki.

478
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:54,399
Please, take your time.

479
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:06,211
I'm really sorry.

480
00:29:07,646 --> 00:29:10,616
About not being able
to publish the interview.

481
00:29:11,116 --> 00:29:12,217
Please, don't be.

482
00:29:14,152 --> 00:29:17,689
I'm the one that has to apologize.

483
00:29:18,557 --> 00:29:20,959
No, why would you say that?

484
00:29:22,661 --> 00:29:27,165
My shoulder isn't ready
for me to make a comeback.

485
00:29:28,333 --> 00:29:32,137
But I wanted to make it seem like
I was.

486
00:29:32,671 --> 00:29:34,139
And agreed to the interview.

487
00:29:35,474 --> 00:29:37,009
Why did you do that?

488
00:29:39,845 --> 00:29:44,816
You wanted to compete
for your 7th consecutive championship.

489
00:29:46,852 --> 00:29:47,619
Yes.

490
00:29:49,454 --> 00:29:51,690
I read your coverage notebook.

491
00:29:52,824 --> 00:29:56,528
Your father won the championship
7 times in a row, right?

492
00:29:56,995 --> 00:30:00,899
Yes, and it became my goal.
To be 7-time champion.

493
00:30:03,735 --> 00:30:08,306
Father always says to go beyond him.
That I'm the one to fulfill his dream.

494
00:30:09,641 --> 00:30:11,143
All the time.

495
00:30:15,614 --> 00:30:18,684
He and I trained hard together
all these years.

496
00:30:20,118 --> 00:30:24,189
It's thanks to him
that I was able to come this far.

497
00:30:26,024 --> 00:30:26,925
So...

498
00:30:29,428 --> 00:30:31,296
I wanted to repay him.

499
00:30:32,464 --> 00:30:34,533
For me,
winning 7 consecutive championships

500
00:30:34,566 --> 00:30:37,002
was more important than the Olympics.

501
00:30:42,441 --> 00:30:44,910
But reality was harsh.

502
00:30:46,645 --> 00:30:48,980
Ms. Horai saw through me.

503
00:30:50,849 --> 00:30:52,317
You met her?

504
00:30:53,919 --> 00:30:54,686
Yes.

505
00:30:55,821 --> 00:31:00,058
I truly understand
how you feel about your father.

506
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:03,028
- Then...
- But if it's published...

507
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:08,834
The expectations of the public
and your father will rise higher.

508
00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:11,636
What's wrong about that?

509
00:31:12,571 --> 00:31:18,110
If that happens,
you'll force yourself to work harder.

510
00:31:19,311 --> 00:31:23,715
You'll injure yourself to the point
of ending your career.

511
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:29,855
I can't let Miyavi
let that happen to you.

512
00:31:36,328 --> 00:31:40,866
At times, our job has the power
to change people's lives.

513
00:31:42,534 --> 00:31:46,538
But it can also offer a chance
to discover a new dream.

514
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,574
That's what I believe.

515
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,945
Her words made me realize.

516
00:31:55,413 --> 00:31:56,648
She's really impressive.

517
00:32:00,852 --> 00:32:01,620
Well.

518
00:32:04,856 --> 00:32:06,725
Will you take a look at these?

519
00:32:07,659 --> 00:32:10,395
It's a copy of the final draft.

520
00:32:11,396 --> 00:32:12,898
It's the proof sheet.

521
00:32:13,598 --> 00:32:17,169
It's printed exactly as it would be
in a magazine.

522
00:32:17,202 --> 00:32:19,838
But I've read the text.

523
00:32:20,238 --> 00:32:22,007
I want you to see it like a magazine.

524
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:27,913
You know, flip the pages
and see which pictures went where.

525
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:33,018
Editors work really hard
to make the perfect layout.

526
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:38,557
How the editor feels
really affects how the pages end up.

527
00:33:06,251 --> 00:33:09,988
My dream of becoming
7th consecutive champion

528
00:33:31,877 --> 00:33:34,813
Why the World Championships?
What comes next?

529
00:33:37,148 --> 00:33:38,416
It's wonderful.

530
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:45,123
I...

531
00:33:46,892 --> 00:33:49,261
I'll make a full recovery
and come back.

532
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:53,031
I couldn't achieve what my father did.

533
00:33:54,466 --> 00:33:58,336
But my judo career
is far from being over.

534
00:34:03,475 --> 00:34:05,977
Ms. Horai really got me this time.

535
00:34:06,011 --> 00:34:10,081
But it was thanks to your notebook
that I understood what she meant.

536
00:34:10,415 --> 00:34:12,550
Don't go through my stuff.

537
00:34:12,584 --> 00:34:14,185
I thought it was amazing.

538
00:34:15,287 --> 00:34:18,857
Ms. Mitsuki's passion
towards judo and modeling.

539
00:34:19,624 --> 00:34:23,261
I really understood how you wanted
to make a feature out of it.

540
00:34:24,496 --> 00:34:25,330
Yeah, well.

541
00:34:25,931 --> 00:34:29,634
I needed to take a step back.
You made me realize that.

542
00:34:30,468 --> 00:34:33,505
Gosh, you're making me blush.

543
00:34:33,538 --> 00:34:35,473
That hurt.

544
00:34:35,507 --> 00:34:36,608
What for?

545
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:38,677
I'm going back now.

546
00:34:59,764 --> 00:35:00,932
Suzuki!

547
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:08,139
Come during these hours

548
00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:10,275
It's until tomorrow.

549
00:35:25,857 --> 00:35:27,025
I'm going home.

550
00:35:27,525 --> 00:35:30,061
Sawako Kobayakawa
as my first interviewee?

551
00:35:30,095 --> 00:35:31,696
It's too much for me!

552
00:35:31,730 --> 00:35:32,998
You can do it.

553
00:35:33,031 --> 00:35:35,834
You have to,
or we won't make it in time.

554
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:39,571
Just think of her as a potato.

555
00:35:39,604 --> 00:35:43,775
She's a potato. Sawako Kobayakawa
is a potato. Imagine it.

556
00:35:44,075 --> 00:35:46,778
Sawako Kobayakawa is a potato.

557
00:35:47,078 --> 00:35:49,014
- Sawako...
- I can't.

558
00:35:49,047 --> 00:35:51,483
Neither can I.

559
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:52,817
We're doomed.

560
00:35:54,052 --> 00:35:55,286
Sorry I'm late.

561
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:56,521
Mr. Nakazawa!

562
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:58,523
I'll do the interview.

563
00:35:59,190 --> 00:36:00,625
The studio and staff are ready.

564
00:36:01,559 --> 00:36:03,428
Thanks. Will you come with me?

565
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:06,564
- I'm going.
- Bye.

566
00:36:06,598 --> 00:36:07,399
Good luck!

567
00:36:11,469 --> 00:36:16,307
Will you tell us why you decided
to become a global economy analyst?

568
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:20,278
When I was at Harvard University...

569
00:36:21,212 --> 00:36:22,180
I see.

570
00:36:27,519 --> 00:36:30,422
It's here!
The pictures and the audio data.

571
00:36:30,455 --> 00:36:33,224
Click it, open it! Hurry, hurry.

572
00:36:33,258 --> 00:36:35,026
What's the password?

573
00:36:35,060 --> 00:36:36,361
How do I...?

574
00:36:36,394 --> 00:36:38,396
You can't even do that?

575
00:36:39,964 --> 00:36:40,732
Ms. Kazumi?

576
00:36:40,765 --> 00:36:42,400
Mr. Nakazawa called us.

577
00:36:42,434 --> 00:36:46,037
Heard you brought him around.
Good job, Suzuki.

578
00:36:46,071 --> 00:36:48,373
How much of the layout is done?

579
00:36:48,873 --> 00:36:49,707
None yet...

580
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:51,776
We don't have time, you know.

581
00:36:51,810 --> 00:36:52,644
I'm sorry.

582
00:36:52,677 --> 00:36:56,381
Shiori and Ms. Rika,
can you transcribe the data?

583
00:36:56,781 --> 00:37:00,251
Asuka, Yui, and Mr. Tada.
get started on the text.

584
00:37:00,285 --> 00:37:02,153
Yui, help me select the pics too.

585
00:37:02,187 --> 00:37:04,456
Wada, we'll work on Nakazawa's pages.

586
00:37:04,489 --> 00:37:06,558
You guys finish your own pages.

587
00:37:06,591 --> 00:37:07,759
Mr. Handa.

588
00:37:08,359 --> 00:37:11,329
We've already finished them at home.

589
00:37:16,334 --> 00:37:17,535
- Yes...
- Shut up!

590
00:37:21,206 --> 00:37:23,374
Nakazawa, thought of the headlines?

591
00:37:24,142 --> 00:37:25,043
I will now.

592
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:26,344
Help me out.

593
00:37:27,412 --> 00:37:29,347
It just might work out.

594
00:37:31,015 --> 00:37:33,518
All thanks to you, Mr. Ogasawara.

595
00:37:34,352 --> 00:37:35,120
Me?

596
00:37:39,824 --> 00:37:42,961
We haven't arranged
for a proofreader, have we?

597
00:37:45,430 --> 00:37:46,798
Actually...

598
00:37:49,167 --> 00:37:51,436
I'm formerly a proofreader.

599
00:38:20,965 --> 00:38:21,866
Please.

600
00:38:37,982 --> 00:38:39,150
I'm nervous.

601
00:38:40,251 --> 00:38:41,119
It'll be fine.

602
00:39:20,758 --> 00:39:22,627
OK with corrections

603
00:39:23,294 --> 00:39:24,162
It's okayed!

604
00:39:28,666 --> 00:39:30,435
We're done!

605
00:39:30,468 --> 00:39:31,669
Good work.

606
00:39:31,703 --> 00:39:33,738
All we do is wait for the printing.

607
00:39:33,771 --> 00:39:34,839
Hey.

608
00:39:36,641 --> 00:39:38,810
I'm sorry for the trouble I caused.

609
00:39:40,445 --> 00:39:41,279
Nah.

610
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:44,482
You all did a great job.

611
00:39:45,984 --> 00:39:47,352
I'll never forget this incredible day.

612
00:39:47,986 --> 00:39:50,021
Let's all drink to this!

613
00:39:54,296 --> 00:39:55,798
Will you join us, Ms. Horai?

614
00:39:56,932 --> 00:39:57,933
Thought not.

615
00:40:00,035 --> 00:40:01,303
Good work.

616
00:40:01,837 --> 00:40:03,872
- Did she just say...?
- Yeah.

617
00:40:05,708 --> 00:40:08,811
Have a taxi ready
tomorrow morning at ten.

618
00:40:10,946 --> 00:40:11,914
Yes!

619
00:40:17,686 --> 00:40:20,055
He won't be there today.

620
00:40:25,394 --> 00:40:26,862
You'll still make it.

621
00:40:29,264 --> 00:40:31,266
Suzuki, go buy some snacks.

622
00:40:31,533 --> 00:40:32,701
I'll go.

623
00:40:50,152 --> 00:40:51,687
Too late.

624
00:40:53,122 --> 00:40:53,922
Oh?

625
00:40:55,190 --> 00:40:56,325
I remember you.

626
00:40:59,628 --> 00:41:00,796
I thought so.

627
00:41:00,829 --> 00:41:02,531
All right, everyone.

628
00:41:03,031 --> 00:41:04,366
Let's have our 10th toast.

629
00:41:04,399 --> 00:41:05,534
Again?

630
00:41:05,567 --> 00:41:08,437
- All right, cheers.
- Cheers!

631
00:41:15,444 --> 00:41:16,812
So delicious.

632
00:41:18,814 --> 00:41:20,616
I thought it was amazing.

633
00:41:20,916 --> 00:41:24,453
Ms. Mitsuki's passion
towards judo and modeling.

634
00:41:24,820 --> 00:41:28,791
I really understood how you wanted
to make a feature out of it.

635
00:41:37,966 --> 00:41:40,669
Mr. Jun has a shoot today
and can't come.

636
00:41:41,470 --> 00:41:44,006
I'll be in the office,
so take your time.

637
00:41:44,773 --> 00:41:46,041
Thank you.

638
00:42:42,731 --> 00:42:43,765
Is that...?

639
00:42:46,101 --> 00:42:46,902
Saved.

640
00:42:49,571 --> 00:42:50,439
Look.

641
00:42:50,572 --> 00:42:51,874
Fresh paint

642
00:42:53,508 --> 00:42:54,309
No way!

643
00:43:03,819 --> 00:43:05,454
I come here often.

644
00:43:05,754 --> 00:43:07,556
The chicken skin is the best.

645
00:43:09,791 --> 00:43:12,361
Would you have preferred
something fancier?

646
00:43:12,394 --> 00:43:13,595
Not at all.

647
00:43:18,967 --> 00:43:20,168
I like...

648
00:43:24,873 --> 00:43:26,208
I like chicken skin.

649
00:43:27,209 --> 00:43:28,543
Good.

650
00:43:28,944 --> 00:43:29,912
Good work.

651
00:43:30,112 --> 00:43:31,313
Thank you.

652
00:43:36,318 --> 00:43:37,352
It's so cold.

653
00:43:39,755 --> 00:43:41,924
It's starting to snow.

654
00:43:41,957 --> 00:43:42,958
You're back?

655
00:43:43,191 --> 00:43:44,426
The shoot ended early.

656
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:48,096
The girl from the mixer was just here.

657
00:43:48,330 --> 00:43:50,098
What was her name...?

658
00:43:50,966 --> 00:43:51,800
Nami.

659
00:43:52,134 --> 00:43:53,235
Nami Suzuki.

660
00:43:53,602 --> 00:43:54,369
When?

661
00:43:54,569 --> 00:43:56,905
Just now. Like five minutes ago.

662
00:43:57,306 --> 00:43:58,373
Or ten.

663
00:43:59,274 --> 00:44:00,242
Mr. Jun?

664
00:44:02,244 --> 00:44:03,679
You go, dude.

665
00:44:50,525 --> 00:44:51,693
Snow...

666
00:45:02,070 --> 00:45:03,005
Nami!

667
00:45:05,374 --> 00:45:06,241
Junnosuke.

668
00:45:12,714 --> 00:45:14,149
I'm like a choo-choo train.

669
00:45:15,484 --> 00:45:16,752
Are you okay?

670
00:45:17,252 --> 00:45:20,288
No, I feel sick. But I'm okay.

671
00:45:22,057 --> 00:45:23,058
You came.

672
00:45:25,660 --> 00:45:28,363
Yeah, we made the deadline, so.

673
00:45:29,765 --> 00:45:30,799
Thanks.

674
00:45:33,068 --> 00:45:34,703
I'm glad I found you in time.

675
00:45:35,337 --> 00:45:37,005
You ran just for that?

676
00:45:37,606 --> 00:45:39,541
You came all this way for me.

677
00:45:40,876 --> 00:45:43,912
Oh yeah, that picture.

678
00:45:44,146 --> 00:45:45,313
My butt.

679
00:45:46,581 --> 00:45:47,349
You noticed?

680
00:45:47,649 --> 00:45:49,017
How dare you.

681
00:45:51,019 --> 00:45:54,656
Your pictures are all so weird.

682
00:45:55,357 --> 00:45:56,358
Weird?

683
00:45:56,591 --> 00:45:59,227
A weird lady in a weird shirt.

684
00:45:59,261 --> 00:46:01,163
And weird things.

685
00:46:01,196 --> 00:46:03,465
That weird afro wig.

686
00:46:04,466 --> 00:46:07,402
I thought it was something
more proper.

687
00:46:08,336 --> 00:46:10,205
Weren't my pictures proper?

688
00:46:11,206 --> 00:46:13,108
Cicada shells? Come on.

689
00:46:20,015 --> 00:46:21,883
Did I say something funny?

690
00:46:34,463 --> 00:46:35,497
Oh darn.

691
00:47:13,268 --> 00:47:13,635
We'd like to do a feature
in our next issue.

692
00:47:13,635 --> 00:47:15,771
Next episode

693
00:47:15,771 --> 00:47:17,439
You can't say that!

694
00:47:17,472 --> 00:47:19,307
Would you like to help me?

695
00:47:19,341 --> 00:47:20,308
Of course!

696
00:47:20,342 --> 00:47:22,711
She's an incredible boss.

697
00:47:22,744 --> 00:47:25,213
- It's yummy!
- Will you go with me?

698
00:47:25,247 --> 00:47:26,214
Who are you?

699
00:47:26,248 --> 00:47:27,182
Her boyfriend.

700
00:47:27,215 --> 00:47:28,049
Boyfriend?
